The geometric random graph model and the associated partial differential equation suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of "cs.DS" (Data Structures and Algorithms) or "cs.NA" (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the use of optimization techniques and the study of the effect of different penalty parameters suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of "cs.IT" (Information Theory).
